{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Fig. 1 (Example 2), it is difficult to identify the word \"deployed\" as the trigger of a \"Movement.Transport\" event based solely on the semantics of the single sentence.",
    "On the other hand, there are many similar event types in ED tasks.",
    "For example, (\"Transfer.Money\", \"Transfer.Ownership\"), they both mean to transfer things.",
    "Semantic correlations exist between such event types and can be used as context to help event detection.",
    "So we select similar event types and regard them as the context of event semantics.Only event type names cannot accurately express type semantics."
  ]
}